<p style="text-align:justify;">July</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">were informed were the remains of a Way party of Sioux who had been destroyed on that spot about Sixteen Years Since<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Soon after this battle <span style="text-decoration:underline;">600</span> Tents of that Nation appeared before the village with a full determination of revenging the loss of their friends by a total extermination of their enemies <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Les Gros ventres</span>.  The siege lasted fifteen days when they retired leaving behind about Three hundred of their warriors lost in skirmishes<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">We assended to the top of the hill from whence we had a delightful prospect &#8212; the several villages and plantations could be seen distinctly<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">On our return to the Village we found Le Borgn<span class="AddHand-author">e</span>&#8217;s Brother arrived in company with a Schian<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  They came from the camp which they left the day before<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The preliminaries of Peace having been Settled these messengers were sent to invite their friends in order to be present at the definitive <span class="AddHand-author">treaty</span>.  The women were to accompany the men and they were to bring with them articles of exchang &#8212; for dressed skins<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  It seems that the Schians have a particular way of dressing leather which renders it preferable</p>
